"Based on the retrieved social media posts, the following facts and claims regarding Ferguson are summarized using the three-state evidence model:\n\n**Verified-Fact**\n*   **Media Sensitivity and Terminology:** There is significant sensitivity among people in Ferguson regarding media descriptions of \"rioting.\" A verified user notes that behavior accurately described as rioting occurred only on Sunday, implying that subsequent events may have been mischaracterized by media outlets [4].\n\n**Informal-but-Genuine**\n*   **Solidarity and Context:** Verified users express solidarity with Ferguson [3]. Unverified users contextualize the event within a broader pattern, noting that another black man was killed by police in Los Angeles around the same time but received less media attention [5].\n\n**Unverified-Rumour**\n*   **Police Jamming Livestreams:** A claim that police are using jammers to take down livestreams in Ferguson is present but lacks corroboration from other sources or high-trust verification [1].\n*   **Police Report Availability:** A post claims to provide a \"full\" police report on Mike Brown; however, the link is redacted/unavailable in the text, and the claim has low support metrics, making the authenticity and completeness of the document unverified [2]."